<p>But in addition to that, we want <code>speciesCount</code> to be a positive number: we don't want
some funny biologist entering negative 10.</p>
<h2 id="constraint-options">Constraint Options <a class="headerlink" href="beautiful-form-validation#constraint-options" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>On the constraints list, there's one called <code>Range</code>. Check that out.</p>
<p>Ok cool: just like the form field types, you can pass options to the constraints.
The <code>Range</code> constraint has several: <code>min</code>, <code>max</code>, <code>minMessage</code> and <code>maxMessage</code>.
Add <code>@Assert\Range</code> with <code>min=0</code> and <code>minMessage="Negative species! Come on..."</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="254655350d">
