	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-3045938149" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-3045938149" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hi Boran!</p><p>Sanity validation is my word for validation that comes out-of-the-box with specific form fields. For example, if you have a NumberType field and someone types the word "FOOOO" in it, that field will automatically fail validation, even though you didn't add any Assert annotations. Most form fields don't have any built-in validation, but some do :). A lot more about that here: <a href="https://disq.us/url?url=https%3A%2F%2Fknpuniversity.com%2Fscreencast%2Fsymfony-forms%2Fdate-format-sanity-validation%3AVKiZj6sbPaJ3Caaghg_AH4cagY0&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">https://knpuniversity.com/scre...</a></p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
