	                    </div>
	                    <div class="dsq-comment-body" id="dsq-comment-body-3014365179">
	                        <div class="dsq-comment-header">
	                            <span class="dsq-comment-date">2016-11-22</span>
	                            <span class="dsq-commenter-name">Victor Bocharsky</span>
	                        </div>

	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-3014365179" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-3014365179" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Hi Terry,</p><p>Yes, it's possible too: use `validation_groups` option for it like in the next example:</p><p></p><pre><code><br>$form = $this-&gt;createFormBuilder($task)<br>            -&gt;add('task', TextType::class, [<br>                'validation_groups' =&gt; ['YourValidationGroup', 'AnotherValidationGroup'],<br>            ])<br>            -&gt;add('dueDate', DateType::class)<br>            -&gt;add('save', SubmitType::class, array('label' =&gt; 'Create Post'))<br>            -&gt;getForm();  <br></code></pre><p></p><p>Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
	                </li>
