	                    <div class="dsq-comment-body" id="dsq-comment-body-2832888435">
	                        <div class="dsq-comment-header">
	                            <span class="dsq-comment-date">2016-08-11</span>
	                            <span class="dsq-commenter-name">weaverryan</span>
	                        </div>

	                        <div id="dsq-comment-message-2832888435" class="dsq-comment-message">
	                            <div id="dsq-comment-text-2832888435" class="dsq-comment-text">
	                                <p>Excellent! I don't see any fundamental mistakes, and you're actually doing something a little bit complex, with the embedded forms. So, congrats :). I think the problem is that the PersonalPersonal class is the "top-level" class that's being validated. Then, the PersonalMainInfo is "embedded" inside of it. The validation system doesn't automatically validate child objects like this - but if you add @Assert\Valid (<a href="http://disq.us/url?url=http%3A%2F%2Fsymfony.com%2Fdoc%2Fcurrent%2Freference%2Fconstraints%2FValid.html%29%3AmcacH2Aw5P7IWqNn_WyiDK1C04I&amp;cuid=1175718" rel="nofollow noopener">http://symfony.com/doc/current...</a> above the personMainInfo property in PersonalPersonal, it should fix the problem.</p><p>Let me know if it works! Cheers!</p>
	                            </div>
	                        </div>
	                    </div>
	                </li>
